validif (tagcount[Hero.Divine] >= 3 + 1)]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xResBonWa" name="Reserve Bonus (water)" description="+1 competence bonus on caster level for water spells." compset="Special" uniqueness="unique">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="Feat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[ var result as number
 result = 0

 if (#hasfeat[fDrownGlan] <> 0) then
   result += 1
 endif

 if (#hasfeat[fAquaBre] <> 0) then
   result += 1
 endif

 field[CustDesc].text = "+" & result & " competence bonus on caster level for water spells."
 field[xSumm].text = "+" & result & " competence bonus on caster level for water spells."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBatCasDef" name="Battlecaster Defense" description="You have mastered techniques for taking full advantage of spells in melee while remaining unharmed.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Combat Casting, base attack bonus +1, caster level 1st.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The Battlecaster Defense feat allows the use of three tactical maneuvers while spellcasting in melee.\n\n{i}Defensive Targeting{/i}: To use this maneuver, you must use the defensive casting option to cast a spell with a range of touch. If you successfully deliver the spell (that is, you succeed on the melee touch attack) on an enemy who threatens you while you cast it, you gain a +2 bonus on any touch attack you make against that enemy on your next turn.\n\n{i}Practiced Defense{/i}: When you successfully cast a spell defensively in 2 consecutive rounds, you gain a +10 bonus on any Concentration check made to cast a spell defensively in the next round.\n\n{i}Safe Retreat{/i}: When you successfully cast a spell defensively, your movement on your next turn doesn&apos;t provoke attacks of opportunity from any creatures that were threatening you when you cast defensively. (The movement still provokes attacks of opportunity from other creatures normally.)\n\n{b}Special{/b}: These benefits apply equally to characters manifesting psionic powers defensively or to those using spell-like abilities defensively.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Feat" summary="Gain a variety of options when casting defensively." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Tactical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Caster level 1st required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Caster] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +1 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Combat Casting required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fComCast] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBatCasOff" name="Battlecaster Offense" description="You cunningly mix melee combat and spellcasting to increase the potency of both.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Combat Casting or warmage edge, base attack bonus +1, Spellcraft 4 ranks.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The Battlecaster Offense feat allows the use of two tactical maneuvers.\n\n{i}Spell and Sword{/i}: If you deal damage to a foe with a spell, you gain a +1 bonus on your first melee attack roll made against that foe in the next round.\n\n{i}Sword and Spell{/i}: If you make a melee attack against a foe, you gain a +1 bonus to the save DC of the first spell you use against that foe in the next round. This bonus applies only against the foe or foes you attacked, not against any other creatures affected by the spell.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Feat" summary="Gain a variety of options when mix melee att with spells." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Tactical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +1 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Combat Casting or warmage edge required."><![CDATA[childfound[cWMaEdge].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] + #hasfeat[fComCast] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Spellcraft 4 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kSpellcr] >= 4]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBladForce" name="Blade of Force" description="You can surround a weapon with a short-lived aura of force.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As long as you have a 3rd-level or higher force spell available to cast, you can surround a melee weapon or a single piece of ammunition with a thin field of force. Activating this ability is a swift action; you must touch the weapon to be affected as part of the action.\n\nThe next attack made with that weapon, if taken before the end of your next turn, deals an extra 1 point of damage per level of the highest-level force spell you have available to cast. Furthermore, that weapon ignores the miss chance normally granted to an incorporeal creature. If the next attack with that weapon misses, this benefit is lost.\n\nAs a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting force spells.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Feat" summary="Force spl 3rd+, swift, +spl lvl dam &amp; ignore incorp on next weap att." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Reserve"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Wizard"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xResBonFor"></bootstrap>
    <prereq message="Ability to cast 3rd level spells required.">
