  <thing id="fTouchDist" name="Touch of Distraction" description="Your touch briefly clouds the mind of a foe, impeding its efforts.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As long as you have an enchantment spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can cloud the mind of a creature within 30 feet as a standard action. The target takes a &#150;2 penalty on its next single attack roll or Reflex saving throw. If the target makes no attacks or Reflex saves within a number of rounds equal to the level of the highest-level enchantment spell you have available to cast, the effect ends. Multiple uses of this feat don&apos;t stack. This is an enchantment (compulsion), mind-affecting effect.\n\nAs a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting enchantment spells.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Feat" summary="Ench spl 3rd+, stand, foe in 30 ft is -2 to next att/Ref save in spl lvl rds." uniqueness="useronce">
