  <thing id="fUnsetEnch" name="Unsettling Enchantment" description="Your enchantment spells cloud the minds of even those who would otherwise resist their effects.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Spell Focus (enchantment) or enchanter level 1st.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Any foe required to save against an enchantment spell you cast takes a &#150;2 penalty on attack rolls and to AC for 1 round, regardless of the result of the save. This is a mind affecting effect.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: An enchanter can select this feat as a wizard bonus feat.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Feat" summary="Target of ench spell takes -2 to AC and att for 1 rd." uniqueness="useronce">
