  <thing id="cWrlPaSlAg" name="Painful Slumber of Ages (Greater; 6th)" description="You can use {i}endless slumber{/i} as the spell (see page 103). Any creature awakened from this effect by anything other than a successful save takes damage equal to your warlock level (no save).\n\n{B}Endless Slumber:{/b} {i}You put a single subject into a magically induced slumber that lasts indefinitely. Normal stimuli, such as shouting or prodding, are insufficient to wake the subject, but any damage dealt to the subject causes her to rouse immediately. The subject can attempt a new save every 24 hours to awaken early. The subject does not need to eat or drink during this time.{/i}" compset="CustomSpec" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpWrl"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <eval phase="Final" priority="1000"><![CDATA[var DC as number
DC = 16 + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & "(DC" & DC & ")"]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Ability to use Greater Invocations required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[xInvoke].field[Value].value >= 11]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cWrlCasLam" name="Caster&apos;s Lament (Dark; 8th)" description="You can produce a {i}break enchantment{/i} effect (as the spell) with your touch. You can only attempt to affect any single magical effect - an ongoing spell, a permanent transformation, a magic item, or the like - once per 24-hour period.\n\nIn addition, you can use {i}casters lament{/i} to counterspell another caster&apos;s spell (of 7th level or lower) as if casting {i}greater dispel magic.{/i}" compset="CustomSpec" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpWrl"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <eval phase="Final" priority="1000"><![CDATA[field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & "(1d20+" & herofield[tLevel].value & ")"]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Ability to use Dark Invocations required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[xInvoke].field[Value].value >= 16]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="isAssassin" name="Assassin&apos;s Staff" description="This unusually small staff is a potent killer&apos;s tool, enabling an assassin to cast a variety of useful and lethal spells.\n\n{b}Description:{/b} An assassins staff is unusually small in diameter for a staff, more resembling a wooden rod. It has a metal handle or globe on one end, allowing it to pass as a walking stick.\n\nWhen a spell is cast through the staff, the wood darkens further, becoming unnaturally black.\n\n{b}Activation:{/b} An assassin&apos;s staff is a spell trigger item, requiring a standard action to activate.\n\n{b}Effect:{/b} An assassin&apos;s staff allows the wielder to produce the following spell effects:\n\n&#149; {i}pall of twilight{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}vital strike{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}deathsight{/i} (2 charges)\n&#149; {i}unseen strike{/i} (2 charges)\n\n{b}Aura/Caster Level:{/b} Moderate divination and illusion. CL 8th.\n\n{b}Construction:{/b} Craft Staff, {i}deathsight{/i}, {i}unseen strike{/i}, {i}vital strike{/i}, {i}pall of twilight{/i}, 19,500 gp, 1,560 XP, 39 days. \n\n{b}Weight:{/b} 5 lb. \n\n{b}Price:{/b} 39,000 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Staff">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="39000"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="50"/>
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Staff"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xSPalTwi">
      <autotag group="ChargeUse" tag="1"/>
      </bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xSVitStrik">
      <autotag group="ChargeUse" tag="1"/>
      </bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xSDeathsi">
      <autotag group="ChargeUse" tag="2"/>
      </bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xSUnStrike">
      <autotag group="ChargeUse" tag="2"/>
      </bootstrap>
    <eval phase="First">field[gWeight].value = 5</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="isDream" name="Dreamstaff" description="A dreamstaff grants its wielder power over sleep and dreams.\n\n{b}Description:{/b} A dreamstaff is carved of light ash wood and possesses strange marbling patterns that run up and down the length. It is unusually slender and topped with a crystal finial.\n\nThe mottling and marbling seem to shift and writhe when the staff is activated, and the crystal fills with smoky, abstract images that are strangely familiar to the viewer.\n\n{b}Activation:{/b} A dreamstaff is a spell trigger item, requiring a standard action to activate.\n\n{b}Effect:{/b} A dreamstaff allows the wielder to produce the following spell effects:\n\n&#149; {i}deep slumber{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}endless slumber{/i} (2 charges)\n&#149; {i}dream{/i} (3 charges)\n&#149; {i}nightmare{/i} (3 charges)\n\n{b}Aura/Caster Level:{/b} Moderate enchantment and illusion. CL 11th.\n\n{b}Construction:{/b} Craft Staff, {i}dream{/i}, {i}endless slumber{/i}, {i}nightmare{/i}, {i}deep slumber{/i}, 27,000 gp, 2,160 XP, 54 days.\n\n{b}Weight:{/b} 5 lb.\n\n{b}Price:{/b} 54,000 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Staff">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="54000"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="50"/>
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Staff"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xSDepSlumb">
      <autotag group="ChargeUse" tag="1"/>
      </bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xSEndSlum">
      <autotag group="ChargeUse" tag="2"/>
      </bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xSDream">
