  <thing id="isMagebane" name="Magebane Staff" description="Designed for no other purpose than to defeat spellcasters, a magebane staff is a prized weapon of casters who expect to battle their own kind.\n\n{b}Description:{/b} A magebane staff is made of heavy wood, banded at the top and bottom with rune-etched iron. Each staff of this kind functions as a masterwork quarterstaff, and many are enchanted with additional weapon-based abilities.\n\nWhen activated, the staff emits a palpable aura of hostility that only spellcasters can feel. This has no mechanical effect, but it does make casters&#151;particularly arcane casters&#151;uncomfortable.\n\n{b}Activation:{/b} A magebane staff is a spell trigger item, requiring a standard action to activate.\n\n{b}Effect:{/b} A magebane staff allows the wielder to produce the following spell effects:\n\n&#149; {i}arcane turmoil{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}Nystul&apos;s magic aura{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}break enchantment{/i} (2 charges)\n&#149; {i}Otiluke&apos;s suppressing field{/i} (2 charges)\n\n{b}Aura/Caster Level:{/b} Moderate abjuration or strong abjuration (greater). CL 9th.\n\n{b}Construction:{/b} Craft Staff, {i}break enchantment{/i}, {i}arcane turmoil{/i}, {i}Otiluke&apos;s suppressing field{/i}, {i}Nystul&apos;s magic aura{/i}, 18,500 gp, 1,485 XP, 38 days.\n\n{b}Variants:{/b} The exceptionally rare greater version of the magebane staff also includes {i}Mordenkainen&apos;s disjunction{/i} (4 charges). (CL 17th, +9,500 gp, +755 XP, +19 days.)\n\n{b}Weight:{/b} 5 lb.\n\n{b}Price:{/b} 37,000 gp (normal), 56,000 gp (greater).\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Staff">
