  <thing id="isLifeless" name="Staff of Lifeless Touch" description="Favored by necromancers and martial casters, a staff of lifeless touch grants you many of the attack forms of the undead.\n\n{b}Description:{/b} A staff of lifeless touch is constructed entirely of bone. Some versions appear to be made of a single long bone, such as the femur of a giant, while others are clearly constructed from multiple interconnected bones. The staff is topped with a skeletal hand, its fingers bent into a shallow claw.\n\nWhen you cast a spell through the staff, the hand clenches of its own accord, as though attempting to grasp the target.\n\n{b}Activation:{/b} A staff of lifeless touch is a spell trigger item, requiring a standard action to activate.\n\n{b}Effect:{/b} A staff of lifeless touch allows the wielder to produce the following spell effects:\n\n&#149; {i}ghoul touch{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}spectral hand{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}vampiric touch{/i} (2 charges)\n&#149; {i}cryptwarden&apos;s grasp{/i} (3 charges)\n&#149; {i}touch of Vecna{/i} (3 charges)\n\n{b}Aura/Caster Level:{/b} Strong necromancy. CL 13th.\n\n{b}Construction:{/b} Craft Staff, {i}cryptwarden&apos;s grasp{/i}, {i}ghoul touch{/i}, \n{i}spectral hand{/i}, {i}touch of Vecna{/i}, {i}vampiric touch{/i}, 19,125 gp, 1,530 XP, 39 days.\n\n{b}Weight:{/b} 5 lb.\n\n{b}Price:{/b} 38,250 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Staff">
