  <thing id="isTricks" name="Staff of Tricks" description="A staff of tricks allows you to call forth a number of mundane but useful items. It is favored by bards who expect to be lacking vital materials.\n\n{b}Description:{/b} A staff of tricks appears to be a simple, unadorned walking stick. It is capped with decorations, jester&apos;s motley, or whatever fits the persona of its owner.\n\nOther than the fact that the staff seems somewhat lighter than its size would indicate, its appearance offers no trace of its abilities.\n\n{b}Activation:{/b} A staff of tricks is a spell trigger item, requiring a standard action to activate.\n\n{b}Effect:{/b} A staff of tricks allows the wielder to produce the following spell effects:\n\n&#149; {i}summon component{/i} (page 118) (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}summon instrument{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}unseen servant{/i} (1 charge)\n&#149; {i}summon weapon{/i} (page 118) (2 charges)\n\n{b}Aura/Caster Level:{/b} Moderate conjuration. CL 8th.\n\n{b}Construction:{/b} Craft Staff, {i}summon component{/i}, {i}summon instrument{/i}, {i}summon weapon{/i}, {i}unseen servant{/i}, 6,750 gp, 540 XP, 14 days.\n\n{b}Weight:{/b} 3 lb.\n\n{b}Price:{/b} 13,500 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="Staff">
