  <thing id="sWuJArbTra" name="Arboreal Transformation" description="{i}Your subject&apos;s skin splits open, revealing wood and bark. Leaves sprout from his limbs even as he starts to grow.{/i}\n\nYou transform the subject of the spell into a Huge oak tree. For a number of days equal to your caster level, that oak tree animates as a treant (though it can&apos;t animate trees) and serves as you\ncommand. You can either command it to follow you, or you can leave it somewhere with a triggering phrase as described in the {i}liveoak{/i} spell (PH 248).\nWhen the spell&apos;s duration expires, the subject becomes in all respects a normal tree, taking root where it stands if capable.\n\nA creature that succeeds on its saving throw is instead {i}slowed{/i} (as the spell) as his body fights off the transformation from within. When the spell&apos;s duration expires, the subject returns to normal." compset="Spell" summary="Transform your foe into a tree, which temporarily animates and serves you.">
