  <thing id="sClrSeeUnd" name="Seed of Undeath" description="{i}The subject&apos;s face briefly takes on a gaunt, pale look and a death&apos;s-head rictus before returning to normal.{/i}\n\nYou plant a kernel of negative energy in a subject, which is held in check by the positive energy inherent to the subject&apos;s own life force. {i}Seed of undeath{/i} does not, in and of itself, harm the subject. Should the subject die before the spell expires, however, it rises as a zombie 1 round later (as per the {i}animate dead{/i} spell), as long as a sufficient corpse remains.\n\nAny undead created in this manner are automatically under your control. At any given time, you can have a number of HD worth of undead animated through {i}seed of undeath{/i} equal to your own HD, and they count against the maximum number of HD worth of undead you can control at any time (as described under {i}animate dead{/i}).\n\n{i}Material Component:{/i} A black onyx gem worth 25 gp per HD of the subject." compset="Spell" summary="Subject that dies before spell expires rises as a zombie under your command.">
