  <thing id="sAsnMordTB" name="Mordenkainen&apos;s Trusted Bloodhound" description="{i}You conjure a phantom hound, that can track and bring down your prey.{/i}\n\nThis spell functions like {i}Mordenkainen&apos;s faithful hound{/i}, except that the phantom bloodhound created can also track a creature as if it had the Track feat. Its Survival modifier is equal to your caster level for this purpose, but it can&apos;t use the Survival skill for any other tasks. A {i}trusted bloodhound{/i} has a land speed equal to yours, and can move at full speed without taking a penalty on Survival checks to track.\n\nA {i}trusted bloodhound{/i} can&apos;t attack, provide a flank, or have any other effect on combat. However, as a standard action, you can instruct a {i}trusted bloodhound{/i} to serve as a watchdog; in this role it functions identically to {i}Mordenkainen&apos;s faithful hound{/i}, except that its attack bonus equals your caster level. You can command a {i}trusted bloodhound{/i} to resume its tracking again as a standard action." compset="Spell" summary="Create a ferocious hound that tracks and attacks foes.">
