  <thing id="sBrdFalLie" name="False Lie" description="{i}Your subject takes on a shifty, dishonest demeanor.{/i}\n\nFalse lie causes the subject to appear dishonest and deceptive. Sense Motive checks made against the subject take a &#150;10 penalty, and any failure convinces the observer that the subject is lying, even if she is not. Anyone who casts a spell that reveals lies (such as {i}discern lie{/i}) can attempt a caster level check (DC 11 + your caster level); if this fails, the spell registers the individual as lying even when she is not.\n\n{i}Material Component:{/i} A serpent&apos;s tongue." compset="Spell" summary="Subject seems to be lying, both to Sense Motive and divinations, even when she is not.">
