  <thing id="sWizPriTor" name="Prickling Torment" description="{i}Angry red boils spread across the skin of your enemy.{/i}\n\nThis spell causes the subject&apos;s skin to erupt in a blistering rash accompanied by a maddening itch. An affected creature is sickened while the spell lasts. In addition, if the creature takes any actions on its turn other than free, swift, or immediate actions, it takes 1d8 points of damage at the end of its turn.\n\nWhile affected by this spell, a creature takes a &#150;2 penalty on saves to resist the distraction effect of any creature of the swarm subtype (in addition to the save penalty from the spell&apos;s sickening effect).\n\nIf a subject under the effect of {i}prickling torment{/i} is targeted by {i}fever dream{/i} (see page 104), the two spells interact to create a greater effect. See the {i}fever dream{/i} spell for details." compset="Spell" summary="Target is sickened, takes damage whenever it acts.">
