  <thing id="sDrdDeaLah" name="Deadly Lahar" description="{i}A rushing torrent of liquid rock bursts from the ground, washing over your foes.{/i}\n\nYou create a liquid landslide of moltenhot volcanic material. All creatures in the area of the spell take 10d6 points of fire damage. Additionally, those creatures are coated in a thick layer of the viscous substance, slowing them (as the {i}slow{/i} spell) for the next 3 rounds and dealing an additional 5d6 points of fire damage per round. A successful Reflex save reduces the initial damage by half and prevents the slow effect and the additional damage." compset="Spell" summary="Create a wave of molten volcanic rock that sticks to creatures.">
