  <thing id="sSorDwnBur" name="Dawn Burst" description="{i}A globe of brilliant radiance erupts silently, as though the light of dawn had arisen.{/i}\n\nAll creatures in the area glow with light equivalent to a torch for the duration of the spell, making hiding difficult and even revealing the location of invisible creatures. (Invisible creatures are still considered to have concealment.)\n\nIn addition, undead and creatures within the area that have light sensitivity or light blindness take 1d6 points of damage, +1 point of damage per caster level (maximum +5). A successful Reflex save halves this damage." compset="Spell" summary="Illuminate all creatures in 10-foot radius; deal damage to light-sensitive creatures.">
