  <thing id="sSorRetIma" name="Retributive Image" description="{i}As though drawn straight from your imagination, the image you envision springs into existence.{/i}\n\nYou create an image or scene, which can incorporate not only sight but sound, smell, and thermal effects. This effect functions in all respects like {i}major image{/i}, except that the illusion is a pattern rather than a figment, and thus has a mind-affecting element to it. Anyone who successfully disbelieves the illusion endures a mental backlash that deals 1d6 points of damage +1 point of damage per caster level (maximum +15) and is dazed for 1 round. A successful Will save halves the damage and negates the dazed effect." compset="Spell" summary="Created illusion deals damage to those who disbelieve it.">
