  <thing id="sSorPriAur" name="Prismatic Aura" description="{i}You are surrounded in a flashing aura of multiple colors.{/i}\n\nThe {i}prismatic aura{/i} spell obscures your image, offering you concealment. In addition, any creature that hits you with a nonreach melee weapon is subject to a random prismatic effect. Roll 1d8 and consult the table under {i}prismatic spray{/i} (PH 264); reroll any result of 8, since a {i}prismatic aura{/i} can&apos;t generate two effects at once. Each time an effect is expended, that color disappears from the aura (reroll if it comes up again on the table). Thus a {i}prismatic aura{/i} can affect a maximum of seven attackers before it disappears, and the spell ends. An attacker is entitled to any applicable saves, and spell resistance applies to this effect." compset="Spell" summary="Shield of colors offers concealment and damages your attackers.">
