  <thing id="sSorUnFoID" name="Unyielding Form of Inevitable Death" description="{i}Your flesh turns into solid onyx, and your muscled fists crackle with the unbridled power of thunder and lightning.{/i}\n\nYou take the form of a marut (MM 159), including the full plate armor normally worn by such a creature. You gain 50 temporary hit points, which disappear at the end of the spell&apos;s duration. You can use each of the marut&apos;s at-will spell-like abilities (such as {i}dimension door{/i}) once per casting of the spell, but you don&apos;t gain access to any of the marut&apos;s 1/day or 1/week spell-like abilities (such as {i}chain lightning{/i} or {i}earthquake{/i}). See the Polymorph Subschool sidebar on page 91 for more details." compset="Spell" summary="You take the form of a marut.">
