  <thing id="sSorPriBow" name="Prismatic Bow" description="{i}A glittering, flashing longbow, containing every hue of the rainbow, appears in your hands.{/i}\n\nA {i}prismatic bow{/i} functions as a +1 longbow; in addition, once per round you can choose to imbue an arrow shot from it with one of the seven colors of the bow, chosen from the list of colors created by prismatic spray (PH 264). In addition to its normal effect, the arrow has the same effect as the corresponding beam from {i}prismatic spray{/i} (including blindness for 2d4 rounds if the target has 8 HD or fewer). Saves and spell resistance apply to this effect as normal for {i}prismatic spray{/i}.\n\nOnce you fire an arrow, the corresponding color disappears from the bow, and you can&apos;t select that color again during this particular casting of the spell. When the duration ends or when you have used the effects of all seven colors, the bow vanishes.\n\nYou are automatically considered proficient with a {i}prismatic bow{/i}.\n\nNo one else can use your {i}prismatic bow{/i}, though you need not carry it at all times (you can stow it, drop it, or even hand it to another character to hold). If you cast this spell a second time while a previous version is still in effect, the first {i}prismatic bows{/i} duration ends." compset="Spell" summary="Creates bow that allows seven attacks, each with a different prismatic effect.">
