  <thing id="sSorPriDel" name="Prismatic Deluge" description="{i}In a blinding shower of light, you call an enormous, painfully bright rainbow from the heavens.{/i}\n\nThis spell produces a column of colors resembling the end of a rainbow. Every creature in the area is affected as though by the {i}prismatic spray{/i} spell (PH 264): blinded for 2d4 rounds if 8 HD or fewer, and you roll 1d8 on the {i}prismatic spray{/i} table to see what color affects which target." compset="Spell" summary="Call down a prismatic effect over a wide area.">
