  <thing id="sWuJTraMor" name="Transcend Mortality" description="{i}You feel your body surge with mystic power that rivals that of the gods themselves.{/i}\n\n{i}Transcend mortality{/i} was created as a last-ditch effort, a spell to use when all other options have failed. For the duration of the spell, you are all but indestructible.\n\nYou gain the following benefits:\n&#149; Damage reduction 30/epic.\n&#149; Spell resistance equal to 21 + you caster level.\n&#149; Acid, cold, electricity, fire, and sonic resistance 50.\n&#149; Immunity to ability damage, disease, energy drain, poison, and death effects.\n&#149; +10 enhancement bonus on all saving throws.\n&#149; You do not need to eat, drink, or breathe.\n\nAlthough this spell makes you effectively unkillable for the duration, that comes at a horrific price. You gain these benefits by using up all your remaining life force. When the spell ends, you are instantly slain and reduced to a pile of dust (as {i}disintegrate{/i}). This effect allows no save and can&apos;t be prevented by any means, though you can be {i}resurrected{/i} normally afterward." compset="Spell" summary="You are nigh-unkillable for a brief period, but die immediately afterward.">
