~ decrease used secondary custom ability count to offset class special 2nd script
hero.child[cHelpRgr].field[cUsedSp2nd].value -= 1


~ assign user tag used in class special 3rd script
perform hero.assign[User.UpArcFE]</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cvCurBreak" name="Curse Breaker" description="Most paladins use their divinely granted powers to combat diseases that plague their allies. Paladins with an interest in the arcane &#151;particularly those who battle necromancers&#151; sometimes prefer to learn to counteract the effects of magical curses.\n\n{b}Class{/b}: Paladin.\n\n{b}Level{/b}: 6th.\n\n{b}Special Requirement{/b}: Knowledge (arcana) 1 rank.\n\n{b}Replaces{/b}: You do not gain the {i}remove disease{/i} spell-like ability or any later improvement of that ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: At 6th level, you can produce a {i}remove curse{/i} effect, as the spell, once per week. You can use this ability one additional time per week for every three levels beyond 6th (twice per week at 9th, three times at 12th, and so forth).\n\nBeginning at 12th level, you can spend two of your weekly uses to produce a {i}break enchantment{/i} effect, as the spell.\n\nThese are spell-like abilities.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
