    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpWiz"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cvSoulStri" name="Soulwarp Strike" description="The traditional monk seeks balance in body, mind, and soul, and through this equilibrium gains various combat talents. A monk who learns the secret of the soulwarp strike masters an arcane talent of necromancy that infects her enemy&apos;s ki, producing an effect akin to terrible sickness.\n\n{b}Class{/b}: Monk.\n\n{b}Level{/b}: 1st.\n\n{b}Special Requirement{/b}: Knowledge (arcana) 1 rank.\n\n{b}Replaces{/b}: You do not gain the monk bonus feat normally acquired at 1st level.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You know how to channel necromantic energy into your unarmed strikes. You must declare that you are using this ability before you make your attack roll (thus, a failed attack roll ruins the attempt). In addition to dealing its normal damage, your unarmed strike renders any living creature nauseated for 1 round, or sickened for 1 round if it succeeds on a Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Wis modifier).\n\nYou can use this ability a number of times per day equal to your monk level, and no more than once per round. Creatures immune to necromancy effects (such as constructs) are unaffected by this ability.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="cvLevel" value="1"/>
    <arrayval field="cvBonFtMod" index="0" value="-1"/>
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="ClVaryName" tag="Append"/>
    <tag group="ClassSkill" tag="kKnowArcan"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cMnkSouStr"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="varies" thing="cHelpMnk"/>
    <evalrule phase="PreLevel" priority="10000" message="Knowledge Arcana rank 1 required."><![CDATA[validif (#skillranks[kKnowArcan] >= 1)]]></evalrule>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMnkSouStr" name="Soulwarp Strike" description="You know how to channel necromantic energy into your unarmed strikes. You must declare that you are using this ability before you make your attack roll (thus, a failed attack roll ruins the attempt). In addition to dealing its normal damage, your unarmed strike renders any living creature nauseated for 1 round, or sickened for 1 round if it succeeds on a Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Wis modifier).\n\nYou can use this ability a number of times per day equal to your monk level, and no more than once per round. Creatures immune to necromancy effects (such as constructs) are unaffected by this ability." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Channel necromantic energy into your unarmed strikes.">
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMnk"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var DC as number

DC = 10 + #totallevelcount[]/2
DC = round(DC, 0, -1)
DC += hero.child[aWIS].field[aModBonus].value

field[livename].text = field[name].text & " (DC" & DC & ")"]]></eval>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="10000" index="2">var charges as number

charges = #levelcount[Monk]

field[hTotal].value = charges</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cvMnkSpRef" name="Spell Reflection" description="Many masters of stealth share the signature talent to avoid explosive blasts of magical energy. It takes only a little training, however, to twist this defensive flair into the ability to reflect magical attacks back upon their creator&#148;\n\n{b}Class{/b}: Monk, ranger, rogue, or scout. Level: 2nd (monk or rogue), 5th (scout), or 9th (ranger).\n\n{b}Special Requirement{/b}: Knowledge (arcana) 1 rank.\n\n{b}Replaces{/b}: You do not gain evasion. (If you would later gain improved evasion as a special ability, you gain evasion instead.)\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You gain the supernatural ability to reflect magical attacks back on their caster. If an enemy misses with a spell or spell-like ability aimed at you, you can use an immediate action to redirect the effect back at its originator. The spell or ability attacks the original caster (who makes a new attack roll using the same modifier as the original attack). If it hits, the caster is subject to the normal effect of the spell or ability.\n\nFor example, if a 3rd-level wizard missed you with a {i}scorching ray{/i}, you could use an immediate action to redirect the ray back to the wizard. The wizard would immediately make a new ranged attack roll (using the same modifier) against his own touch AC; if the attack succeeds, the {i}scorching ray{/i} deals its normal damage to the wizard.\n\nThis effect applies only to spells and spell-like abilities that require an attack roll. Other spells and spell-like abilities that affect a target aren&apos;t subject to this reflection.\n\nIf a single spell or ability misses you more than once at the same time (such as {i}scorching ray{/i} cast by a high-level caster), you can redirect each portion of the spell that missed. Using the example above, if you were missed by two of the three rays from an 11th-level wizard&apos;s {i}scorching ray{/i} spell, you could redirect only those two rays (but not the one that hit).\n\nYou can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 1 + your Dex modifier (minimum 1/day).\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Mage" compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="cvLevel" value="2"/>
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="ClVaryName" tag="Append"/>
    <tag group="ClassSkill" tag="kKnowArcan"/>
    <tag group="SpcReplace" tag="cMnkEvas"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cMnkSpeRef"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="varies" thing="cHelpMnk"/>
    <evalrule phase="PreLevel" priority="10000" message="Knowledge Arcana rank 1 required."><![CDATA[validif (#skillranks[kKnowArcan] >= 1)]]></evalrule>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMnkSpeRef" name="Spell Reflection" description="You gain the supernatural ability to reflect magical attacks back on their caster. If an enemy misses with a spell or spell-like ability aimed at you, you can use an immediate action to redirect the effect back at its originator. The spell or ability attacks the original caster (who makes a new attack roll using the same modifier as the original attack). If it hits, the caster is subject to the normal effect of the spell or ability.\n\nFor example, if a 3rd-level wizard missed you with a {i}scorching ray{/i}, you could use an immediate action to redirect the ray back to the wizard. The wizard would immediately make a new ranged attack roll (using the same modifier) against his own touch AC; if the attack succeeds, the {i}scorching ray{/i} deals its normal damage to the wizard.\n\nThis effect applies only to spells and spell-like abilities that require an attack roll. Other spells and spell-like abilities that affect a target aren&apos;t subject to this reflection.\n\nIf a single spell or ability misses you more than once at the same time (such as {i}scorching ray{/i} cast by a high-level caster), you can redirect each portion of the spell that missed. Using the example above, if you were missed by two of the three rays from an 11th-level wizard&apos;s {i}scorching ray{/i} spell, you could redirect only those two rays (but not the one that hit).\n\nYou can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 1 + your Dex modifier (minimum 1/day)." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Deflect spells back at their caster.">
    <usesource source="CompMage"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMnk"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
